<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-135-169 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 833 528</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  June 4 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft acquires tools for software security. (license with RSAData Security)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mallory, Jim.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Licenses)RSA Data Security Inc. (Licenses).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Topic:     LicensingAlgorithmsSecurity software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MICROSOFT ACQUIRES TOOLS FOR SOFTWARE SECURITY 06/04/91 REDMOND, WASHINGTON,U.S.A., 1991 JUN 4 (NB) -- Microsoft has announced that it has acquired alicense to RSA Data Security's technology.andP;  The license gives Microsoft thecapability to incorporate advanced security features into its products.andM;Commenting on the license, Bill Gates, Microsoft chairman, said: &quot;RSA'stechnology will allow us to incorporate advanced security features in ourproducts and create a secure computing environment for our customers.&quot;andM;Microsoft will use the technology to provide privacy and authentication ofsensitive user data, as well as to detect viruses and secure softwaredistribution.andM;Microsoft said it will also participate in, as well as endorse, RSA's effortto establish interoperability.andP;  In a program sponsored by Novell, Lotus, SunMicrosystems and Digital, RSA has completed development of an interoperablestandard for the use of the company's technology.andM;Gates praised RSA's program, noting that &quot;interoperability between productsincorporating RSA, including products from different vendors, is important ifusers are to realize the true value of this technology.&quot; He also encouragedother vendors to adopt and support RSA's program.andM;RSA was founded in 1982 by three professors at Massachusetts Institute ofTechnology (MIT), who invented the RSA security algorithm.andP;  The RSA algorithmhas been proposed as a standard in the CCITT, the Consultive Committee forInternational Telephony and Telegraphy, as well as the InternationalOrganization for Standardization (ISO), and Standards Australia.andM;RSA's products include a software toolkit for developers, as well asimplementation of the Internet Privacy Enhanced Mail Standard.andM;(Jim Mallory/19910604/Press Contact: Brenda Hansen, Microsoft, 206-882- 8080)</TEXT></DOC>